Reasoning: The paper proposes a new framework for assigning values to data points in the context of an underlying data distribution, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of Shapley values and machine learning models suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the focus on data valuation and data markets suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The statistical properties of the proposed framework and the algorithmic developments suggest a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
